
[1]whirligig

   WHIRLIGIG, n. [whirl and gig.]

   1. A toy which children spin or whirl round.

   2. In military antiquities, an instrument for punishing petty
   offenders, as sutlers, brawling women, &c.; a kind of wooden cage
   turning on a pivot, in which the offender was whirled round with great
   velocity.
